Description: Wooden club or stick, curved, with knob at one end.
Curator's comments: Found inside the coffin of Sebekaa (Berlin 45) in a sepulchral chamber at the 'Small Temple of Isis', Thebes, in 1823: Catalogue of Giovanni d'Athanasi's collection of Egyptian Antiquities now exhibiting at Exeter Hall, p. 20.
Acquisition notes: 'A.692', written on the object, identifies it as lot 692 in the d'Athanasi sale, Sotheby's, London, 1837.
